<Author>TimCollier
<Content>Very Disappointing I booked our stay in Barcelona for one week before we left on a Western Mediterranean Cruise. Our idea was to be close to Las Rambas and close to the Port.When we arrived, we were presented with what appeared to be a shabby hole in the wall on Carrer Rauric. It does not have an elevator. The room can only be called Spartan. The view was of a window of the building directly across the street. The streets in the Gothic Quarter are very narrow--of course this is the atmosphere that I had wanted.The continental breakfast was fine. But, the hotel is definitely not in a safe area of the city. Walking back to the hotel at about 1 a.m. on the first night, we were 'almost' robbed by locals.The next morning, we relocated to the Hotel Axel. Much better area and still close to everything. Much better accommodations. Furthermore; during the rest of the week, not a single incident of attempted robbery.While the Hotel California is located in a very central location and the accommodations are 'acceptable', if you can afford better, chose another hotel. 
