<Author>DebbieBeck
<Content>Great value We arrived before our cruise 11/7/2008 and stayed for one night and upon return stayed 11/15 and 11/16. Our dealings with the staff (in English) was prompt and truthful. They quoted the room rate in Euros and gave the total including taxes and fees. There was never a question about the rate when we arrived. So helpful and service oriented. No elevator but they carried our heavy luggage upstairs for us. We did not have problems with the noise. Enjoyed the balcony in each room we had. Very clean and safe. Front entry doors are locked at all times and they have 24 hr desk attendance. Provided a n electric jack and hair dryer. You must ask at the desk. Considering the difference in American hotels and Euro hotels this was very good and did incl a good continental breakfast which was incl and many you pay extra. Bed hard but tolerable. We were only there to sleep at night and went sight seeing during day. This has location, location, location right off Las Ramblas. We rode the train from airport and took metro to hotel and walked with our luggage from metro to hotel. We planned to take the blue bus from Las Ramblas to the ship but never could find the stop so we walked with our luggage from hotel to the ship. Very long way. Would not advise this. Upon return we found the blue bus stop at the Columbus monument. You can't use your metro/train ticket on the blue bus. If you plan to sight see Barcelona either buy the tour bus ticket or buy a T10. The T 10 can be used on the train and metro and is good for an extended period of time. I'd stay again with them! Very thoughtful of their guests! 
