<Content>Great Place to Stay We stayed one week at the Hotel California in Barcelona. The hotel is in a great location, just off La Rambles and close to the Plaze Rieal. There are lots of bars, tapas bars, shops, museums, and places to eat near by. The staff at the hotel were great. They were very friendly and helpful. They greeted us with a smile every time we came in the door. The rooms are a decent size and the bathroom was great. Our bathroom had a sliding door with a small terrace off of it, which provided lots of natural light to the room. The room had a large closet with lots of shelves and hangers and A/C. It was clean and quiet. The only downfall was the very hard bed. The price of the room was 85 Euros a night, which included breakfast. Breakfast was standard with cereal, breads, coffee, tea, juice and hot chocolate. The long hours for breakfast (8-11) were great. This was by far the best room we stayed in on our trip (out of 4) and the best value as well. I would stay there again! 
