<Author>LancashirePals
<Content>Noisy but reasonable value We stayed for 3 nights, booked via their website. Arrangements were excellent with e-mails (in English) being answered / actioned very quickly; they asked for a confirmation one week before arrival. Reception very helpful but be aware there is no lift to any of the 3 floors. We were offered a choice of rooms and settled for room 103 (double on first floor on corner of the property, at the front). The self-service Continental breakfast was plentiful (but no ham, cheese, yoghurt or fruit). The rooms were clean but they could do with a bit more 'tender loving care' and some basic investment / up-grade of the mattress, top sheets and furniture; hot water was always available. The hotel location is very good on a street off the Ramblas. Good Irish Bars locally (try Molly's Fair City) and try the Schilling Bar for coffeee  beer as some on the street were rip offs (especially one close to / on the same side as the Schilling offering tapas). Do not eat at the Compestella Restaurant on this street as they could not get you out of the place quick enough (you only got an apple for your sweet on the tourist menu for 16 Euros!). For a quick, cheap lunch or snack try the Pans chain of sandwich shops. The best way to see the city is the Official Tourist Bus, but do not expect anyone to be courteous and queue as they charge on and even laugh at you when you complain; also use the vouchers they give you on the bus for discounts to attractions and for food. The only complaint we had was about the noise in the street outside the hotel - do not expect a good night's sleep as locals were drinking cans of beer outside the hotel (just in the street) up to 5.00 a.m. each evening / morning. The hotel is supposed to be double glazed with air-conditioning - the first doesn't work as you can hear every word spoken / shouted, but at least the air conditioning did. I would not like to stay here in the main holiday period in the summer months. In summary, it is worth the money for what you get and where it is. We will not be returning to Barcelona and three days was enough to do what we wanted to do / see. 
