<Content>Safe, clean and very good value for money This hotel is situated very centrally indeed, being a stone's throw from the Ramblas, and a five-minute walk to Plaza de Catalunya, which is the transport hub of the city of Barcelona. I have stayed in many hotels in Barcelona (I lived there for a year and often go back to visit) and in my opinion this offers the best value for money of any I have ever stayed in.When you build your expectations, bear in mind that this is a 2 star, budget hotel in the centre of Barcelona, which is a vibrant, 24-hour European party city. Some of the reviews of the hotel I have just read for this page are laughably naive. You will not get satellite TV, you will not see a large American-style lobby and there is no room service - if you want these luxuries, don't expect to get them from a budget hotel, and book into a larger hotel nearby. The hotel is run very efficiently from a small front desk, by very friendly staff.The hotel is located at the heart of the city, where the Gothic Quarter meets the Chinese Quarter (also known as the Raval). This is not a tranquil, tree-lined part of the city - it's the hot, lively, noisy, seedy heart of the city. If you want to have a hotel with staid respectability, go and stay up on the Diagonal or in Gracia, which are the yuppie areas of town.A lot is made of this hotel's gay friendly atmosphere on certain web pages, but this is misleading - the hotel is welcoming of ALL people, not just gay people. I am a gay man myself but the majority of people who stay here represent a regular cross section of travellers - the hotel is not seedy.The rooms are a good size for a budget hotel but most importantly they are clean which, even now that there is so much competition in the hotel trade, is a luxury in this hotel category in Barcelona. I have had no problem with the space of my room on any visit. The bathrooms are not mouldy or musty, and are clean and to a similar standard as the bedrooms. I have had no reason to use the electrical points but I find it hard to believe that the wiring would cause any device to explode, as one reviewer has mentioned. More likely is that the reviewer has used an inappropriate adapter - European plugs deliver 240V and not 110V as in the US.I hope this balances up some of the negative comments. In brief, this hotel is not a luxury establishment but it is safe and clean, with a friendly atmosphere, and it's based in the most exciting part of the city. 
