<Content>Such a lovely place, such a noisy place Barcelona's Hotel California is central to the activity of the Old Town, the world famous Ramblas avenue is approximately 100 yards away.This is a small, two star hotel, no elevators so if you are on the third floor it is a bit of a climb. The hotel reception operates 24 hours and the staff all speak good English and were charming and very helpful. Rooms are simple but very clean, all with TV, efficient air-con and en-suite bathrooms.Not expensive for central Barcelona and if you don't want the inclusive breakfast (selection of cereals, pastries, rolls, juice, tea, coffee available from 7am to 11am) there are good restaurants close by serving everything you could wish for.The Hotel California (and when you check in the guy actually says 'Welcome to the Hotel California!') is in a very narrow side street so no view worth talking about even if you have one of the rooms with a tiny balcony. The entrance to this street was (and we were informed has been for quite some time) the dwelling place for several homeless people. They are not threatening in any way but when the local bars close (and there is an Irish bar right next to the entrance to the hotel) these vagrants become very noisy as do the many young tourists. With bars in Barcelona (and there are lots of bars in Barcelona) closing at any time between 2am and 5am don't expect a lot of sleep. 
